    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-04-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <head>No. 501.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Schuyler</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St.
                                    Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 23, 1875</date>.
                            (Received May 14.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 107.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that, according
                        to the “Odessa Messenger,” on the initiative of the minister of domains, the
                        Mennonites, called into the military service by the conscription, will be
                        organized into companies of workmen and employed in forest cultivation on
                        the lands belonging to the state in South Russia.</p>
                <p>An official of the minister of domains has been sent to Odessa to organize
                        this useful enterprise, and in general to study the question of
                        forest-planting in the country.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EUGENE SCHUYLER.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
